              <div class="panel-pane pane-block pane-views-crime-alerts-block-1">
               <h2 class="pane-title">
                Crime/Safety Alerts
               </h2>
               <div class="pane-content">
                <div class="view view-crime-alerts view-id-crime_alerts view-display-id-block_1 view-dom-id-1">
                 <div class="view-empty">
                  <p>
                   There are no active crime/safety alerts.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                 <div class="more-link">
                  <a href="/crime_alerts">
                   more
                  </a>
                 </div>
                 <div class="view-footer">
                  <p>
                   <a href="/archived_crime_alerts">
                    Click here for archived Crime/Safety Alerts, beginning February 2007.
                   </a>
                  </p>
                  <p>
                   Two ways to report information about a crime or suspicious activity:
                  </p>
                  <p>
                   Call 262.2150, or go online using this link
                   <a href="/report-crime">
                    Report Crime Information Online
                   </a>
                   .
                  </p>
                  <p>
                   Notification to the campus of serious crimes is required by federal law.
                  </p>
                 </div>
                </div>
               </div>
              </div>
              <div class="panel-region-separator">
              </div>
              <div class="panel-pane pane-custom pane-1">
               <h2 class="pane-title">
                Appalachian Police Officer Development Program (APDP)
               </h2>
               <div class="pane-content">
                <p>
                 The Appalachian Police Officer Development Program (APDP), the only program of its kind in North Carolina, is a two-year program designed to equip students with the knowledge, skills and training to become law enforcement officers, all while they are completing their undergraduate or graduate degrees at Appalachian State University.
                </p>
                <p>
                 <strong>
                  Deadline for applications for the 2019-2020 academic year is Thursday, Feb. 28, 2019.
                 </strong>
                </p>
                <p style="text-align: right;">
                 <a href="/apdp">
                  Learn more
                 </a>
                </p>
               </div>
              </div>
             </div>
            </div>
           </div>
          </div>
         </div>
